#. <section id="vagga"><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.41" id="41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: sūkavaggo (bj) | paṇihitavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.2"
msgid "5. Paṇihitaacchavagga"
msgstr "5. A Spike"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.3"
msgid "41"
msgstr "41"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41.1"></a>
#. VAR: bhecchati → bhejjati (si) | bhijjissati (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā micchāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena "
"vā pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhecchati lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti "
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the wrong way. "
"If you trod on it with hand or foot, there’s no way it could break the skin "
"and produce blood."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.3"
msgid "Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa."
msgstr "Because the spike is pointing the wrong way."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu micchāpaṇihitena cittena avijjaṃ "
"bhecchati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is pointing the wrong way cannot "
"break ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.6"
msgid "Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti."
msgstr "Because their mind is pointing the wrong way.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.7"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.42" id="42"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.8"
msgid "42"
msgstr "42"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā sammāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena vā "
"pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhecchati lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti "
"ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the right way. "
"If you trod on it with hand or foot, it may well break the skin and produce "
"blood."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.3"
msgid "Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa."
msgstr "Because the spike is pointing the right way."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu sammāpaṇihitena cittena avijjaṃ "
"bhecchati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is pointing the right way can break "
"ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.6"
msgid "Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti."
msgstr "Because the mind is pointing the right way.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.43" id="43"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.8"
msgid "43"
msgstr "43"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43.1"></a>
#. VAR: Idhāhaṃ → idāhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ paduṭṭhacittaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto "
"paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person whose mind is "
"corrupted, I understand:"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.2"
msgid ""
"‘imamhi ce ayaṃ samaye puggalo kālaṃ kareyya, yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ "
"niraye’."
msgstr ""
"‘If this person were to die right now, they would be cast down to hell.’"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.4"
msgid "Cittaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, paduṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "Because their mind is corrupted."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.5"
msgid ""
"Cetopadosahetu pana, bhikkhave, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Depravity of mind is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body "
"breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the "
"underworld, hell.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.6"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.44" id="44"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.7"
msgid "44"
msgstr "44"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44.1"></a>
#. VAR: Idhāhaṃ → idāhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ pasannacittaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person whose mind is "
"confident, I understand:"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.2"
msgid ""
"‘imamhi ce ayaṃ samaye puggalo kālaṃ kareyya, yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ "
"sagge’."
msgstr ""
"‘If this person were to die right now, they would be raised up to heaven.’"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.4"
msgid "Cittaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, pasannaṃ."
msgstr "Because their mind is clear."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.5"
msgid ""
"Cetopasādahetu pana, bhikkhave, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Clarity of mind is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body "
"breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.45" id="45"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.7"
msgid "45"
msgstr "45"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45.1"></a>
#. VAR: luḷito → lulito (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: sippisambukampi → sippikasambukampi (mr)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udakarahado āvilo luḷito kalalībhūto tattha cakkhumā "
"puriso tīre ṭhito na passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakaṭhalampi "
"macchagumbampi carantampi tiṭṭhantampi."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose, mendicants, there was a lake that was cloudy, murky, and muddy. A "
"person with good eyesight standing on the bank would not see the mussel "
"shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying "
"still."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.3"
msgid "Āvilattā, bhikkhave, udakassa."
msgstr "Because the water is clouded."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu āvilena cittena attatthaṃ vā "
"ñassati paratthaṃ vā ñassati ubhayatthaṃ vā ñassati uttariṃ vā manussadhammā "
"alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikarissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, that a mendicant whose mind is clouded would know what’s "
"for their own good, the good of another, or the good of both; or that they "
"would realize any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of "
"the noble ones: this is not possible."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.6"
msgid "Āvilattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti."
msgstr "Because their mind is clouded.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.46" id="46"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.8"
msgid "46"
msgstr "46"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo tattha cakkhumā "
"puriso tīre ṭhito passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakaṭhalampi macchagumbampi "
"carantampi tiṭṭhantampi."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose, mendicants, there was a lake that was transparent, clear, and "
"unclouded. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would see the "
"mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or "
"staying still."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.3"
msgid "Anāvilattā, bhikkhave, udakassa."
msgstr "Because the water is unclouded."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu anāvilena cittena attatthaṃ vā "
"ñassati paratthaṃ vā ñassati ubhayatthaṃ vā ñassati uttariṃ vā manussadhammā "
"alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikarissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, that a mendicant whose mind is not clouded would know what’"
"s for their own good, the good of another, or the good of both; or that they "
"would realize any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of "
"the noble ones: this is possible."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.6"
msgid "Anāvilattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti."
msgstr "Because their mind is unclouded.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.47" id="47"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.8"
msgid "47"
msgstr "47"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici rukkhajātānaṃ phandano tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati yadidaṃ mudutāya ceva kammaññatāya ca."
msgstr ""
"“Just as, mendicants, the <i>papra</i> is said to be the best kind of tree "
"in terms of its pliability and workability,"

msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.2"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nāññaṃ ekadhammampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ "
"bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ mudu ca hoti kammaññañca yathayidaṃ cittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"so too, I do not see a single thing that’s as pliable and workable as the "
"mind, when it is developed and cultivated."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.3"
msgid ""
"Cittaṃ, bhikkhave, bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ mudu ca hoti kammaññañca hotī”ti."
msgstr "A mind that is developed and cultivated is pliable and workable.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.48" id="48"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.5"
msgid "48"
msgstr "48"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.1"
msgid ""
"“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekadhammampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ lahuparivattaṃ "
"yathayidaṃ cittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I do not see a single thing that’s as quick to change as the "
"mind."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.2"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, upamāpi na sukarā yāva lahuparivattaṃ cittan”ti."
msgstr ""
"So much so that it’s not easy to give a simile for how quickly the mind "
"changes.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.49" id="49"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.4"
msgid "49"
msgstr "49"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.1"
msgid "“Pabhassaramidaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ."
msgstr "“This mind, mendicants, is radiant."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.2"
msgid "Tañca kho āgantukehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhan”ti."
msgstr "But it’s corrupted by passing corruptions.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.50" id="50"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.4"
msgid "50"
msgstr "50"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50.1"></a>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.1"
msgid "“Pabhassaramidaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ."
msgstr "“This mind, mendicants, is radiant."

msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.2"
msgid "Tañca kho āgantukehi upakkilesehi vippamuttan”ti."
msgstr "And it is freed from passing corruptions.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.3"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.4"
msgid "Paṇihitaacchavaggo pañcamo."
msgstr ""
